			<ns0:name>kschi...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/108470876877739532758/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">The current model of registers includes: (1) The set of 16 general purpose registers; (2) the APSR flags NZCV; and (3) Whether we even try to model the APSR flags NZCV.

However, the last condition(3), is no longer even needed. The concept was only used in hand-written actual classes, as a simplification for modeling. By adding this concept, other code must treat this simplification as a special case, and complicates the code.

Since we are no longer using the concept, it is better to remove it and simplify the implementation of the ARM validator.
